pokemon.flavorText: Calyrex is known in legend as a king that ruled over Galar in ancient times. It has the power to cause hearts to mend and plants to spring forth.

pokemon.name: wyrdeer
pokemon.flavorText: The black orbs shine with an uncanny light when the Pokémon is erecting invisible barriers. The fur shed from its beard retains heat well and is a highly useful material for winter clothing.

pokemon.name: kleavor
pokemon.flavorText: A violent creature that fells towering trees with its crude axes and shields itself with hard stone. If one should chance upon this Pokémon in the wilds, one's only recourse is to flee.

pokemon.name: ursaluna
pokemon.flavorText: I believe it was Hisui's swampy terrain that gave Ursaluna its burly physique and newfound capacity to manipulate peat at will.

pokemon.name: basculegion-male
pokemon.flavorText: Clads itself in the souls of comrades that perished before fulfilling their goals of journeying upstream. No other species throughout all Hisui's rivers is Basculegion's equal.

pokemon.name: sneasler
pokemon.flavorText: Because of Sneasler's virulent poison and daunting physical prowess, no other species could hope to best it on the frozen highlands. Preferring solitude, this species does not form packs.

pokemon.name: overqwil
pokemon.flavorText: Its lancelike spikes and savage temperament have earned it the nickname ”sea fiend.” It slurps up poison to nourish itself.

pokemon.name: enamorus-incarnate
pokemon.flavorText: When it flies to this land from across the sea, the bitter winter comes to an end. According to legend, this Pokémon's love gives rise to the budding of fresh life across Hisui.

pokemon.name: sprigatito
pokemon.flavorText: The sweet scent its body gives off mesmerizes those around it. The scent grows stronger when this Pokémon is in the sun.

pokemon.name: floragato
pokemon.flavorText: The hardness of Floragato’s fur depends on the Pokémon’s mood. When Floragato is prepared to battle, its fur becomes pointed and needle sharp.

pokemon.name: meowscarada
pokemon.flavorText: With skillful misdirection, it rigs foes with pollen-packed flower bombs. Meowscarada sets off the bombs before its foes realize what’s going on.

pokemon.name: fuecoco
pokemon.flavorText: Its flame sac is small, so energy is always leaking out. This energy is released from the dent atop Fuecoco’s head and flickers to and fro.

pokemon.name: crocalor
pokemon.flavorText: The valve in Crocalor’s flame sac is closely connected to its vocal cords. This Pokémon utters a guttural cry as it spews flames every which way.

pokemon.name: skeledirge
pokemon.flavorText: Skeledirge’s gentle singing soothes the souls of all that hear it. It burns its enemies to a crisp with flames of over 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit.

pokemon.name: quaxly
pokemon.flavorText: Its strong legs let it easily swim around in even fast-flowing rivers. It likes to keep things tidy and is prone to overthinking things.

pokemon.name: quaxwell
pokemon.flavorText: The hardworking Quaxwell observes people and Pokémon from various regions and incorporates their movements into its own dance routines.

pokemon.name: quaquaval
pokemon.flavorText: Dancing in ways that evoke far-away places, this Pokémon mesmerizes all that see it. Flourishes of its decorative water feathers slice into its foes.

pokemon.name: lechonk
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon spurns all but the finest of foods. Its body gives off an herblike scent that bug Pokémon detest.

pokemon.name: oinkologne-male
pokemon.flavorText: It entrances female Pokémon with the sweet, alluring scent that wafts from all over its body.

pokemon.name: tarountula
pokemon.flavorText: The thread it secretes from its rear is as strong as wire. The secret behind the thread’s strength is the topic of ongoing research.

pokemon.name: spidops
pokemon.flavorText: Spidops covers its territory in tough, sticky threads to set up traps for intruders.

pokemon.name: nymble
pokemon.flavorText: It’s highly skilled at a fighting style in which it uses its jumping capabilities to dodge incoming attacks while also dealing damage to opponents.

pokemon.name: lokix
pokemon.flavorText: It uses its normally folded third set of legs when in Showdown Mode. This places a huge burden on its body, so it can’t stay in this mode for long.

pokemon.name: pawmi
pokemon.flavorText: The pads of its paws are electricity-discharging organs. Pawmi fires electricity from its forepaws while standing unsteadily on its hind legs.

pokemon.name: pawmo
pokemon.flavorText: Pawmo uses a unique fighting technique in which it uses its forepaws to strike foes and zap them with electricity from its paw pads simultaneously.

pokemon.name: pawmot
pokemon.flavorText: Pawmot’s fluffy fur acts as a battery. It can store the same amount of electricity as an electric car.

pokemon.name: tandemaus
pokemon.flavorText: The pair sticks together no matter what. They split any food they find exactly in half and then eat it together.

pokemon.name: maushold-family-of-four
pokemon.flavorText: The larger pair protects the little ones during battles. When facing strong opponents, the whole group will join the fight.

pokemon.name: fidough
pokemon.flavorText: The yeast in Fidough’s breath is useful for cooking, so this Pokémon has been protected by people since long ago.

pokemon.name: dachsbun
pokemon.flavorText: The surface of this Pokémon’s skin hardens when exposed to intense heat, and its body has an appetizing aroma.

pokemon.name: smoliv
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon converts nutrients into oil, which it stores in the fruit on its head. It can easily go a whole week without eating or drinking.

pokemon.name: dolliv
pokemon.flavorText: It basks in the sun to its heart’s content until the fruits on its head ripen. After that, Dolliv departs from human settlements and goes on a journey.

pokemon.name: arboliva
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon drives back enemies by launching its rich, aromatic oil at them with enough force to smash a boulder.

pokemon.name: squawkabilly-green-plumage
pokemon.flavorText: Green-feathered flocks hold the most sway. When they’re out searching for food in the mornings and evenings, it gets very noisy.

pokemon.name: nacli
pokemon.flavorText: The ground scrapes its body as it travels, causing it to leave salt behind. Salt is constantly being created and replenished inside Nacli’s body.

pokemon.name: naclstack
pokemon.flavorText: It compresses rock salt inside its body and shoots out hardened salt pellets with enough force to perforate an iron sheet.

pokemon.name: garganacl
pokemon.flavorText: Many Pokémon gather around Garganacl, hoping to lick at its mineral-rich salt.

pokemon.name: charcadet
pokemon.flavorText: Its firepower increases when it fights, reaching over 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit. It likes berries that are rich in fat.

pokemon.name: armarouge
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon clads itself in armor that has been fortified by psychic and fire energy, and it shoots blazing fireballs.

pokemon.name: ceruledge
pokemon.flavorText: An old set of armor steeped in grudges caused this Pokémon’s evolution. Ceruledge cuts its enemies to pieces without mercy.

pokemon.name: tadbulb
pokemon.flavorText: It floats using the electricity stored in its body. When thunderclouds are around, Tadbulb will float higher off the ground.

pokemon.name: bellibolt
pokemon.flavorText: What appear to be eyeballs are actually organs for discharging the electricity generated by Bellibolt’s belly-button dynamo.

pokemon.name: wattrel
pokemon.flavorText: These Pokémon make their nests on coastal cliffs. The nests have a strange, crackling texture, and they’re a popular delicacy.

pokemon.name: kilowattrel
pokemon.flavorText: It uses its throat sac to store electricity generated by its wings. There’s hardly any oil in its feathers, so it is a poor swimmer.

pokemon.name: maschiff
pokemon.flavorText: Its well-developed jaw and fangs are strong enough to crunch through boulders, and its thick fat makes for an excellent defense.

pokemon.name: mabosstiff
pokemon.flavorText: Mabosstiff loves playing with children. Though usually gentle, it takes on an intimidating look when protecting its family.

pokemon.name: shroodle
pokemon.flavorText: To keep enemies away from its territory, it paints markings around its nest using a poisonous liquid that has an acrid odor.

pokemon.name: grafaiai
pokemon.flavorText: Each Grafaiai paints its own individual pattern, and it will paint that same pattern over and over again throughout its life.

pokemon.name: bramblin
pokemon.flavorText: Not even Bramblin knows where it is headed as it tumbles across the wilderness, blown by the wind. It loathes getting wet.

pokemon.name: brambleghast
pokemon.flavorText: Brambleghast wanders around arid regions. On rare occasions, mass outbreaks of these Pokémon will bury an entire town.

pokemon.name: toedscool
pokemon.flavorText: Though it looks like Tentacool, Toedscool is a completely different species. Its legs may be thin, but it can run at a speed of 30 mph.

pokemon.name: toedscruel
pokemon.flavorText: It coils its 10 tentacles around prey and sucks out their nutrients, causing the prey pain. The folds along the rim of its head are a popular delicacy.

pokemon.name: klawf
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon lives on sheer cliffs. It sidesteps opponents’ attacks, then lunges for their weak spots with its claws.

pokemon.name: capsakid
pokemon.flavorText: Traditional Paldean dishes can be extremely spicy because they include the shed front teeth of Capsakid among their ingredients.

pokemon.name: scovillain
pokemon.flavorText: The green head has turned vicious due to the spicy chemicals stimulating its brain. Once it goes on a rampage, there is no stopping it.

pokemon.name: rellor
pokemon.flavorText: It rolls its mud ball around while the energy it needs for evolution matures. Eventually the time comes for it to evolve.

pokemon.name: rabsca
pokemon.flavorText: An infant sleeps inside the ball. Rabsca rolls the ball soothingly with its legs to ensure the infant sleeps comfortably.

pokemon.name: flittle
pokemon.flavorText: It spends its time running around wastelands. If anyone steals its beloved berries, it will chase them down and exact its revenge.

pokemon.name: espathra
pokemon.flavorText: It emits psychic power from the gaps between its multicolored frills and sprints at speeds greater than 120 mph.

pokemon.name: tinkatink
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon pounds iron scraps together to make a hammer. It will remake the hammer again and again until it’s satisfied with the result.

pokemon.name: tinkatuff
pokemon.flavorText: These Pokémon make their homes in piles of scrap metal. They test the strength of each other’s hammers by smashing them together.

pokemon.name: tinkaton
pokemon.flavorText: The hammer tops 220 pounds, yet it gets swung around easily by Tinkaton as it steals whatever it pleases and carries its plunder back home.

pokemon.name: wiglett
pokemon.flavorText: Though it looks like Diglett, Wiglett is an entirely different species. The resemblance seems to be a coincidental result of environmental adaptation.

pokemon.name: wugtrio
pokemon.flavorText: A variety of fish Pokémon, Wugtrio was once considered to be a regional form of Dugtrio.

pokemon.name: bombirdier
pokemon.flavorText: Bombirdier uses the apron on its chest to bundle up food, which it carries back to its nest. It enjoys dropping things that make loud noises.

pokemon.name: finizen
pokemon.flavorText: Its water ring is made from seawater mixed with a sticky fluid that Finizen secretes from its blowhole.

pokemon.name: palafin-zero
pokemon.flavorText: Its physical capabilities are no different than a Finizen’s, but when its allies are in danger, it transforms and powers itself up.

pokemon.name: varoom
pokemon.flavorText: The steel section is Varoom’s actual body. This Pokémon clings to rocks and converts the minerals within into energy to fuel its activities.

pokemon.name: revavroom
pokemon.flavorText: Revavroom viciously threatens others with the sound of its exhaust. It sticks its tongue out from its cylindrical mouth and sprays toxic fluids.

pokemon.name: cyclizar
pokemon.flavorText: It can sprint at over 70 mph while carrying a human. The rider’s body heat warms Cyclizar’s back and lifts the Pokémon’s spirit.

pokemon.name: orthworm
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon lives in arid deserts. It maintains its metal body by consuming iron from the soil.

pokemon.name: glimmet
pokemon.flavorText: Glimmet’s toxic mineral crystals look just like flower petals. This Pokémon scatters poisonous powder like pollen to protect itself.

pokemon.name: glimmora
pokemon.flavorText: Glimmora’s petals are made of crystallized poison energy. It has recently become evident that these petals resemble Tera Jewels.

pokemon.name: greavard
pokemon.flavorText: This friendly Pokémon doesn’t like being alone. Pay it even the slightest bit of attention, and it will follow you forever.

pokemon.name: houndstone
pokemon.flavorText: A lovingly mourned Pokémon was reborn as Houndstone. It doesn’t like anyone touching the protuberance atop its head.

pokemon.name: flamigo
pokemon.flavorText: Thanks to a behavior of theirs known as “synchronizing,” an entire flock of these Pokémon can attack simultaneously in perfect harmony.

pokemon.name: cetoddle
pokemon.flavorText: It lives in frigid regions in pods of five or so individuals. It loves the minerals found in snow and ice.

pokemon.name: cetitan
pokemon.flavorText: Ice energy builds up in the horn on its upper jaw, causing the horn to reach cryogenic temperatures that freeze its surroundings.

pokemon.name: veluza
pokemon.flavorText: Veluza has excellent regenerative capabilities. It sheds spare flesh from its body to boost its agility, then charges at its prey.

pokemon.name: dondozo
pokemon.flavorText: It treats Tatsugiri like its boss and follows it loyally. Though powerful, Dondozo is apparently not very smart.

pokemon.name: tatsugiri-curly
pokemon.flavorText: Tatsugiri is an extremely cunning Pokémon. It feigns weakness to lure in prey, then orders its partner to attack.

pokemon.name: annihilape
pokemon.flavorText: It imbues its fists with the power of the rage that it kept hidden in its heart. Opponents struck by these imbued fists will be shattered to their core.

pokemon.name: clodsire
pokemon.flavorText: It lives at the bottom of ponds and swamps. It will carry Wooper on its back and ferry them across water from one shore to the other.

pokemon.name: farigiraf
pokemon.flavorText: The hardened head from the tail protects the head of the main body as Farigiraf whips its long neck around to headbutt enemies.

pokemon.name: dudunsparce-two-segment
pokemon.flavorText: It drives enemies out of its nest by sucking in enough air to fill its long, narrow lungs, then releasing the air in an intense blast.

pokemon.name: kingambit
pokemon.flavorText: Though it commands a massive army in battle, it’s not skilled at devising complex strategies. It just uses brute strength to keep pushing.

pokemon.name: great-tusk
pokemon.flavorText: This creature resembles a mysterious Pokémon that, according to a paranormal magazine, has lived since ancient times.

pokemon.name: scream-tail
pokemon.flavorText: It resembles a mysterious Pokémon described in a paranormal magazine as a Jigglypuff from one billion years ago.

pokemon.name: brute-bonnet
pokemon.flavorText: It bears a slight resemblance to a Pokémon described in a dubious magazine as a cross between a dinosaur and a mushroom.

pokemon.name: flutter-mane
pokemon.flavorText: It has similar features to a ghostly pterosaur that was covered in a paranormal magazine, but the two have little else in common.

pokemon.name: slither-wing
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon somewhat resembles an ancient form of Volcarona that was introduced in a dubious magazine.

pokemon.name: sandy-shocks
pokemon.flavorText: It slightly resembles a Magneton that lived for 10,000 years and was featured in an article in a paranormal magazine.

pokemon.name: iron-treads
pokemon.flavorText: Sightings of this Pokémon have occurred in recent years. It resembles a mysterious object described in an old expedition journal.

pokemon.name: iron-bundle
pokemon.flavorText: It resembles a mysterious object mentioned in an old book. There are only two reported sightings of this Pokémon.

pokemon.name: iron-hands
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon shares many similarities with Iron Hands, an object mentioned in a certain expedition journal.

pokemon.name: iron-jugulis
pokemon.flavorText: It’s possible that Iron Jugulis, an object described in an old book, may actually be this Pokémon.

pokemon.name: iron-moth
pokemon.flavorText: No records exist of this species being caught. Data is lacking, but the Pokémon’s traits match up with an object described in an old book.

pokemon.name: iron-thorns
pokemon.flavorText: Some of its notable features match those of an object named within a certain expedition journal as Iron Thorns.

pokemon.name: frigibax
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon lives in forests and craggy areas. Using the power of its dorsal fin, it cools the inside of its nest like a refrigerator.

pokemon.name: arctibax
pokemon.flavorText: It attacks with the blade of its frozen dorsal fin by doing a front flip in the air. Arctibax’s strong back and legs allow it to pull off this technique.

pokemon.name: baxcalibur
pokemon.flavorText: It launches itself into battle by flipping upside down and spewing frigid air from its mouth. It finishes opponents off with its dorsal blade.

pokemon.name: gimmighoul
pokemon.flavorText: It lives inside an old treasure chest. Sometimes it gets left in shop corners since no one realizes it’s actually a Pokémon.

pokemon.name: gholdengo
pokemon.flavorText: It has a sturdy body made up of stacked coins. Gholdengo overwhelms its enemies by firing coin after coin at them in quick succession.

pokemon.name: wo-chien
pokemon.flavorText: It drains the life-force from vegetation, causing nearby forests to instantly wither and fields to turn barren.

pokemon.name: chien-pao
pokemon.flavorText: The hatred of those who perished by the sword long ago has clad itself in snow and become a Pokémon.

pokemon.name: ting-lu
pokemon.flavorText: It slowly brings its exceedingly heavy head down upon the ground, splitting the earth open with huge fissures that run over 160 feet deep.

pokemon.name: chi-yu
pokemon.flavorText: The envy accumulated within curved beads that sparked multiple conflicts has clad itself in fire and become a Pokémon.

pokemon.name: roaring-moon
pokemon.flavorText: According to an article in a dubious magazine, this Pokémon has some connection to a phenomenon that occurs in a certain region.

pokemon.name: iron-valiant
pokemon.flavorText: It’s possible that this is the object listed as Iron Valiant in a certain expedition journal.

pokemon.name: koraidon
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon resembles Cyclizar, but it is far burlier and more ferocious. Nothing is known about its ecology or other features.

pokemon.name: miraidon
pokemon.flavorText: This seems to be the Iron Serpent mentioned in an old book. The Iron Serpent is said to have turned the land to ash with its lightning.

pokemon.name: walking-wake
pokemon.flavorText: It resembles an illustration published in a paranormal magazine, said to be a depiction of a super-ancient Suicune.

pokemon.name: iron-leaves
pokemon.flavorText: According to the few eyewitness accounts that exist, it used its shining blades to julienne large trees and boulders.

pokemon.name: dipplin
pokemon.flavorText: The head sticking out belongs to the fore-wyrm, while the tail belongs to the core-wyrm. The two share one apple and help each other out.

pokemon.name: poltchageist
pokemon.flavorText: Poltchageist looks like a regional form of Sinistea, but it was recently discovered that the two Pokémon are entirely unrelated.

pokemon.name: sinistcha
pokemon.flavorText: It prefers cool, dark places, such as the back of a shelf or the space beneath a home's floorboards. It wanders in search of prey after sunset.

pokemon.name: okidogi
pokemon.flavorText: Okidogi is a ruffian with a short temper. It can pulverize anything by swinging around the chain on its neck.

pokemon.name: munkidori
pokemon.flavorText: Munkidori keeps itself somewhere safe while it toys with its foes, using psychokinesis to induce intense dizziness.

pokemon.name: fezandipiti
pokemon.flavorText: Fezandipiti beats its glossy wings to scatter pheromones that captivate people and Pokémon.

pokemon.name: ogerpon
pokemon.flavorText: This mischief-loving Pokémon is full of curiosity. It battles by drawing out the type-based energy contained within its masks.

pokemon.name: archaludon
pokemon.flavorText: It digs holes on mountains, searching for food. It’s so durable that being caught in a cave-in won’t faze it.

pokemon.name: hydrapple
pokemon.flavorText: These capricious syrpents have banded together. On the rare occasion that their moods align, their true power is unleashed.

pokemon.name: gouging-fire
pokemon.flavorText: It resembles an eerie Pokémon once shown in a paranormal magazine. That Pokémon was said to be an Entei regenerated from a fossil.

pokemon.name: raging-bolt
pokemon.flavorText: It bears resemblance to a Pokémon that became a hot topic for a short while after a paranormal magazine touted it as Raikou's ancestor.

pokemon.name: iron-boulder
pokemon.flavorText: It was named after a mysterious object recorded in an old book. Its body seems to be metallic.

pokemon.name: iron-crown
pokemon.flavorText: There was supposedly an incident in which it launched shining blades to cut everything around it to pieces. Little else is known about it.

pokemon.name: terapagos
pokemon.flavorText: It’s thought that this Pokémon lived in ancient Paldea until it got caught in seismic shifts and went extinct.

pokemon.name: pecharunt
pokemon.flavorText: Its peach-shaped shell serves as storage for a potent poison. It makes poisonous mochi and serves them to people and Pokémon.

pokemon.name: deoxys-attack
pokemon.flavorText: Deoxys emerged from a virus that came from space. It is highly intelligent and wields psychokinetic powers. This Pokémon shoots lasers from the crystalline organ on its chest.

pokemon.name: deoxys-defense
pokemon.flavorText: Deoxys emerged from a virus that came from space. It is highly intelligent and wields psychokinetic powers. This Pokémon shoots lasers from the crystalline organ on its chest.

pokemon.name: deoxys-speed
pokemon.flavorText: Deoxys emerged from a virus that came from space. It is highly intelligent and wields psychokinetic powers. This Pokémon shoots lasers from the crystalline organ on its chest.

pokemon.name: wormadam-sandy
pokemon.flavorText: When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon’s body. The cloak is never shed.

pokemon.name: wormadam-trash
pokemon.flavorText: When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon’s body. The cloak is never shed.

pokemon.name: shaymin-sky
pokemon.flavorText: When the turning of seasons brings the cruel winter to its end and the joyous people give thanks to the heavens, Shaymin appears and covers the withered land with flowers.

pokemon.name: giratina-origin
pokemon.flavorText: There is one Hisuian verse that tells of a powerful light creating a deep shadow. I imagine that this deep shadow is Giratina.

pokemon.name: rotom-heat
pokemon.flavorText: This bizarre Pokémon appears to be a will-o'-the-wisp powered by electricity. Be wary, as Rotom is both smart and mischievous.

pokemon.name: rotom-wash
pokemon.flavorText: This bizarre Pokémon appears to be a will-o'-the-wisp powered by electricity. Be wary, as Rotom is both smart and mischievous.

pokemon.name: rotom-frost
pokemon.flavorText: This bizarre Pokémon appears to be a will-o'-the-wisp powered by electricity. Be wary, as Rotom is both smart and mischievous.

pokemon.name: rotom-fan
pokemon.flavorText: This bizarre Pokémon appears to be a will-o'-the-wisp powered by electricity. Be wary, as Rotom is both smart and mischievous.

pokemon.name: rotom-mow
pokemon.flavorText: This bizarre Pokémon appears to be a will-o'-the-wisp powered by electricity. Be wary, as Rotom is both smart and mischievous.

pokemon.name: castform-sunny
pokemon.flavorText: Its form changes depending on the weather. The rougher conditions get, the rougher Castform’s disposition!

pokemon.name: castform-rainy
pokemon.flavorText: Its form changes depending on the weather. The rougher conditions get, the rougher Castform’s disposition!

pokemon.name: castform-snowy
pokemon.flavorText: Its form changes depending on the weather. The rougher conditions get, the rougher Castform’s disposition!

pokemon.name: basculin-blue-striped
pokemon.flavorText: Though it differs from other Basculin in several respects, including demeanor—this one is gentle—I have categorized it as a regional form given the vast array of shared qualities.

pokemon.name: darmanitan-zen
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon’s power level rises along with the temperature of its fire, which can reach 2,500 degrees Fahrenheit.

pokemon.name: meloetta-pirouette
pokemon.flavorText: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.

pokemon.name: tornadus-therian
pokemon.flavorText: This storm-stirring Pokémon is said to cause the seasons to turn by whipping up the air. I suspect its humanlike form to be a false one.

pokemon.name: thundurus-therian
pokemon.flavorText: They say this wielder of electricity has waged war with its nemesis, Tornadus, since time immemorial. The lightning bolts it hurls pierce the very earth and enrich the soil.

pokemon.name: landorus-therian
pokemon.flavorText: When the incarnations of wind and of lightning clash, Landorus arrives to quell the conflict. After the tempests and thunderbolts abate, the land is sure to be blessed with bountiful harvests.

pokemon.name: kyurem-black
pokemon.flavorText: It appears that this Pokémon uses its powers over ice to freeze its own body in order to stabilize its cellular structure.

pokemon.name: kyurem-white
pokemon.flavorText: It appears that this Pokémon uses its powers over ice to freeze its own body in order to stabilize its cellular structure.

pokemon.name: keldeo-resolute
pokemon.flavorText: They say that Keldeo must survive harsh battles and fully develop the horn on its forehead before this Pokémon’s true power will awaken.

pokemon.name: meowstic-female
pokemon.flavorText: The defensive instinct of the males is strong. It’s when they’re protecting themselves or their partners that they unleash their full power.

pokemon.name: aegislash-blade
pokemon.flavorText: Its potent spectral powers allow it to manipulate others. It once used its powers to force people and Pokémon to build a kingdom to its liking.

pokemon.name: pumpkaboo-small
pokemon.flavorText: The light that streams out from the holes in the pumpkin can hypnotize and control the people and Pokémon that see it.

pokemon.name: pumpkaboo-large
pokemon.flavorText: The light that streams out from the holes in the pumpkin can hypnotize and control the people and Pokémon that see it.

pokemon.name: pumpkaboo-super
pokemon.flavorText: The light that streams out from the holes in the pumpkin can hypnotize and control the people and Pokémon that see it.

pokemon.name: gourgeist-small
pokemon.flavorText: In the darkness of a new-moon night, Gourgeist will come knocking. Whoever answers the door will be swept off to the afterlife.

pokemon.name: gourgeist-large
pokemon.flavorText: In the darkness of a new-moon night, Gourgeist will come knocking. Whoever answers the door will be swept off to the afterlife.

pokemon.name: gourgeist-super
pokemon.flavorText: In the darkness of a new-moon night, Gourgeist will come knocking. Whoever answers the door will be swept off to the afterlife.

pokemon.name: venusaur-mega
pokemon.flavorText: A bewitching aroma wafts from its flower. The fragrance becalms those engaged in a battle.

pokemon.name: charizard-mega-x
pokemon.flavorText: Its wings can carry this Pokémon close to an altitude of 4,600 feet. It blows out fire at very high temperatures.

pokemon.name: charizard-mega-y
pokemon.flavorText: Its wings can carry this Pokémon close to an altitude of 4,600 feet. It blows out fire at very high temperatures.

pokemon.name: blastoise-mega
pokemon.flavorText: The rocket cannons on its shell fire jets of water capable of punching holes through thick steel.

pokemon.name: alakazam-mega
pokemon.flavorText: The longer Alakazam lives, the larger and heavier its head becomes. Our tests have shown that the strength of its psychic powers correlates positively to the weight of its head.

pokemon.name: gengar-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Possesses potential victims' shadows in an effort to steal away the victims' lives. If your shadow begins to laugh, you must take hold of a protective charm posthaste!

pokemon.name: kangaskhan-mega
pokemon.flavorText: There are records of a lost human child being raised by a childless Kangaskhan.

pokemon.name: pinsir-mega
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon clamps its pincers down on its prey and then either splits the prey in half or flings it away.

pokemon.name: gyarados-mega
pokemon.flavorText: I suspect this Pokémon to be the true identity of a dragon written of in ancient texts, which claimed that it razed an entire village with white-hot beams from its maw.

pokemon.name: aerodactyl-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Aerodactyl’s sawlike fangs can shred skin to tatters—even the skin of Steel-type Pokémon.

pokemon.name: mewtwo-mega-x
pokemon.flavorText: Its DNA is almost the same as Mew’s. However, its size and disposition are vastly different.

pokemon.name: mewtwo-mega-y
pokemon.flavorText: Its DNA is almost the same as Mew’s. However, its size and disposition are vastly different.

pokemon.name: ampharos-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Its tail shines bright and strong. It has been prized since long ago as a beacon for sailors.

pokemon.name: scizor-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Evolved by way of a curious item. The shell covering its body has been shown to be stronger than forged steel.

pokemon.name: heracross-mega
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon has an unparalleled horn. Heracross itself demonstrates tremendous power—it's capable of throwing several people trained in the traditional arts of war at once.

pokemon.name: houndoom-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Identifiable by its eerie howls, people a long time ago thought it was the grim reaper and feared it.

pokemon.name: tyranitar-mega
pokemon.flavorText: The quakes caused when it walks make even great mountains crumble and change the surrounding terrain.

pokemon.name: blaziken-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Blaziken has incredibly strong legs—it can easily clear a 30-story building in one leap. This Pokémon’s blazing punches leave its foes scorched and blackened.

pokemon.name: gardevoir-mega
pokemon.flavorText: It will dedicate itself to defending a master it has come to adore. Its pure white dress, reminiscent of those worn by ladies of nobility, is the dress of one who is willing to risk their life.

pokemon.name: mawile-mega
pokemon.flavorText: It chomps with its gaping mouth. Its huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed.

pokemon.name: aggron-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Long ago, there was a king who wore a helmet meant to resemble the head of an Aggron. He was trying to channel the Pokémon’s strength.

pokemon.name: medicham-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Through the power of meditation, Medicham developed its sixth sense. It gained the ability to use psychokinetic powers. This Pokémon is known to meditate for a whole month without eating.

pokemon.name: manectric-mega
pokemon.flavorText: It rarely appears before people. It is said to nest where lightning has fallen.

pokemon.name: banette-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Resentment at being cast off made it spring into being. Some say that treating it well will satisfy it, and it will once more become a stuffed toy.

pokemon.name: absol-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Because of this Pokémon’s ability to detect danger, people mistook Absol as a bringer of doom.

pokemon.name: garchomp-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Soars across the heavens at blinding speed—a magnificent sight! It has a feral disposition. Utmost caution is required if one meets a Garchomp out in the wilds.

pokemon.name: lucario-mega
pokemon.flavorText: A most gallant-looking creature. It emits energy waves and controls them with precision, using them to sense even faraway beings. I have given the name ”aura” to this power.

pokemon.name: abomasnow-mega
pokemon.flavorText: A powerful Pokémon that can split huge boulders with ease. Dislikes associating with others and chooses to live quietly deep within the mountains, playing with the snow.

pokemon.name: floette-eternal
pokemon.flavorText: It gives its own power to flowers, pouring its heart into caring for them. Floette never forgives anyone who messes up a flower bed.

pokemon.name: latias-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Latias is highly intelligent and capable of understanding human speech. It is covered with a glass-like down. The Pokémon enfolds its body with its down and refracts light to alter its appearance.

pokemon.name: latios-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Latios will only open its heart to a Trainer with a compassionate spirit. This Pokémon can fly faster than a jet plane by folding its forelegs to minimize air resistance.

pokemon.name: swampert-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Swampert predicts storms by sensing subtle differences in the sounds of waves and tidal winds with its fins. If a storm is approaching, it piles up boulders to protect itself.

pokemon.name: sceptile-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Sceptile has seeds growing on its back. They are said to be bursting with nutrients that revitalize trees. This Pokémon raises the trees in a forest with loving care.

pokemon.name: sableye-mega
pokemon.flavorText: It feeds on gemstone crystals. In darkness, its eyes sparkle with the glitter of jewels.

pokemon.name: altaria-mega
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon has a kind disposition, but if it’s provoked, it will threaten opponents with shrill cries before attacking them without mercy.

pokemon.name: gallade-mega
pokemon.flavorText: The blades extending from its elbows are sharper than the finest swords. Its swordsmanship, albeit self-taught, is astonishingly impressive.

pokemon.name: audino-mega
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon has a kind heart. By touching with its feelers, Audino can gauge other creatures’ feelings and physical conditions.

pokemon.name: sharpedo-mega
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon is known as the Bully of the Sea. Any ship entering the waters Sharpedo calls home will be attacked—no exceptions.

pokemon.name: slowbro-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Being bitten by a Shellder shocked this Pokémon into standing on two legs. If the Shellder lets go, it seems Slowbro will turn back into a Slowpoke.

pokemon.name: steelix-mega
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon evolved through use of a strange item. Its body is coated with steel powder and notably hard—not even diamond can leave so much as a scratch.

pokemon.name: pidgeot-mega
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon flies at Mach 2 speed, seeking prey. Its large talons are feared as wicked weapons.

pokemon.name: glalie-mega
pokemon.flavorText: It covers its body with an armor of ice harder than steel. Uses its breath to freeze prey, which it then devours as if they were frozen desserts.

pokemon.name: diancie-mega
pokemon.flavorText: It can instantly create many diamonds by compressing the carbon in the air between its hands.

pokemon.name: metagross-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Metagross is the result of the fusion of two Metang. This Pokémon defeats its opponents through use of its supercomputer-level brain.

pokemon.name: kyogre-primal
pokemon.flavorText: Kyogre is said to be the personification of the sea itself. Legends tell of its many clashes against Groudon, as each sought to gain the power of nature.

pokemon.name: groudon-primal
pokemon.flavorText: Through Primal Reversion and with nature’s full power, it will take back its true form. It can cause magma to erupt and expand the landmass of the world.

pokemon.name: rayquaza-mega
pokemon.flavorText: It flies forever through the ozone layer, consuming meteoroids for sustenance. The many meteoroids in its body provide the energy it needs to Mega Evolve.

pokemon.name: pikachu-rock-star
pokemon.flavorText: Possesses cheek sacs in which it stores electricity. This clever forest-dweller roasts tough berries with an electric shock before consuming them.

pokemon.name: pikachu-belle
pokemon.flavorText: Possesses cheek sacs in which it stores electricity. This clever forest-dweller roasts tough berries with an electric shock before consuming them.

pokemon.name: pikachu-pop-star
pokemon.flavorText: Possesses cheek sacs in which it stores electricity. This clever forest-dweller roasts tough berries with an electric shock before consuming them.

pokemon.name: pikachu-phd
pokemon.flavorText: Possesses cheek sacs in which it stores electricity. This clever forest-dweller roasts tough berries with an electric shock before consuming them.

pokemon.name: pikachu-libre
pokemon.flavorText: Possesses cheek sacs in which it stores electricity. This clever forest-dweller roasts tough berries with an electric shock before consuming them.

pokemon.name: pikachu-cosplay
pokemon.flavorText: Possesses cheek sacs in which it stores electricity. This clever forest-dweller roasts tough berries with an electric shock before consuming them.

pokemon.name: hoopa-unbound
pokemon.flavorText: It is said to be able to seize anything it desires with its six rings and six huge arms. With its power sealed, it is transformed into a much smaller form.

pokemon.name: camerupt-mega
pokemon.flavorText: The humps on Camerupt’s back are formed by a transformation of its bones. They sometimes blast out molten magma. This Pokémon apparently erupts often when it is enraged.

pokemon.name: lopunny-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Its fur is warm and yet remarkably light. This Pokémon kicks as though it were a master of karate, driving back its opponents with ease.

pokemon.name: salamence-mega
pokemon.flavorText: While basking in the joy of flight generally keeps this Pokémon in high spirits, Salamence turns into an uncontrollable menace if something angers it.

pokemon.name: beedrill-mega
pokemon.flavorText: It has three poisonous stingers on its forelegs and its tail. They are used to jab its enemy repeatedly.

pokemon.name: rattata-alola
pokemon.flavorText: Will chew on anything with its fangs. If you see one, you can be certain that 40 more live in the area.

pokemon.name: raticate-alola
pokemon.flavorText: Its hind feet are webbed. They act as flippers, so it can swim in rivers and hunt for prey.

pokemon.name: raticate-totem-alola
pokemon.flavorText: Its hind feet are webbed. They act as flippers, so it can swim in rivers and hunt for prey.

pokemon.name: pikachu-original-cap
pokemon.flavorText: Possesses cheek sacs in which it stores electricity. This clever forest-dweller roasts tough berries with an electric shock before consuming them.

pokemon.name: pikachu-alola-cap
pokemon.flavorText: Possesses cheek sacs in which it stores electricity. This clever forest-dweller roasts tough berries with an electric shock before consuming them.

pokemon.name: raichu-alola
pokemon.flavorText: It can discharge bursts of electricity exceeding 100,000 volts— a single strike with that amount of power would incapacitate one of the Copperajah of my homeland.

pokemon.name: sandshrew-alola
pokemon.flavorText: It burrows into the ground to create its nest. If hard stones impede its tunneling, it uses its sharp claws to shatter them and then carries on digging.

pokemon.name: sandslash-alola
pokemon.flavorText: It climbs trees by hooking on with its sharp claws. Sandslash shares the berries it gathers, dropping them down to Sandshrew waiting below the tree.

pokemon.name: vulpix-alola
pokemon.flavorText: In its belly burns a fire, which Vulpix spits out in the form of fireballs. When young, this Pokémon has but one white tail. As the Pokémon matures, this single tail splits into six.

pokemon.name: ninetales-alola
pokemon.flavorText: The coat of gleaming golden fur is quite magnificent. This species is said to store sacred power in its nine long tails and to live for a millennium.

pokemon.name: diglett-alola
pokemon.flavorText: It burrows through the ground at a shallow depth. It leaves raised earth in its wake, making it easy to spot.

pokemon.name: dugtrio-alola
pokemon.flavorText: These Diglett triplets dig over 60 miles below sea level. No one knows what it’s like underground.

pokemon.name: meowth-alola
pokemon.flavorText: It loves to collect shiny things. If it’s in a good mood, it might even let its Trainer have a look at its hoard of treasures.

pokemon.name: persian-alola
pokemon.flavorText: Its elegant and refined behavior clashes with that of the barbaric Perrserker. The relationship between the two is one of mutual disdain.

pokemon.name: geodude-alola
pokemon.flavorText: Makes its home in mountainous regions, using its arms to climb along harsh mountain roads. Can be troublesome—carelessly kicking one will cause it to fly into a rage and chase after you.

pokemon.name: graveler-alola
pokemon.flavorText: Dwells in holes dug into sheer walls of stone. It enjoys rolling down slopes as though it were a boulder during a rockfall, so keep an eye upward while traversing mountain roads.

pokemon.name: golem-alola
pokemon.flavorText: The rocklike shell is shed each year. The cast-off shell then crumbles, reverting to a mass of soil, which can be spread across fields to promote crop growth.

pokemon.name: grimer-alola
pokemon.flavorText: Made of congealed sludge. It smells too putrid to touch. Even weeds won’t grow in its path.

pokemon.name: muk-alola
pokemon.flavorText: Smells so awful, it can cause fainting. Through degeneration of its nose, it lost its sense of smell.

pokemon.name: exeggutor-alola
pokemon.flavorText: When they work together, Exeggutor’s three heads can put out powerful psychic energy. Cloudy days make this Pokémon sluggish.

pokemon.name: marowak-alola
pokemon.flavorText: When this Pokémon evolved, the skull of its mother fused to it. Marowak’s temperament also turned vicious at the same time.

pokemon.name: greninja-battle-bond
pokemon.flavorText: It appears and vanishes with a ninja’s grace. It toys with its enemies using swift movements, while slicing them with throwing stars of sharpest water.

pokemon.name: greninja-ash
pokemon.flavorText: It appears and vanishes with a ninja’s grace. It toys with its enemies using swift movements, while slicing them with throwing stars of sharpest water.

pokemon.name: zygarde-10-power-construct
pokemon.flavorText: Some say it can change to an even more powerful form when battling those who threaten the ecosystem.

pokemon.name: zygarde-50-power-construct
pokemon.flavorText: Some say it can change to an even more powerful form when battling those who threaten the ecosystem.

pokemon.name: zygarde-complete
pokemon.flavorText: Some say it can change to an even more powerful form when battling those who threaten the ecosystem.

pokemon.name: gumshoos-totem
pokemon.flavorText: Patient by nature, this Pokémon loses control of itself and pounces when it spots its favorite meal—Rattata!

pokemon.name: vikavolt-totem
pokemon.flavorText: If it carries a Charjabug to use as a spare battery, a flying Vikavolt can rapidly fire high-powered beams of electricity.

pokemon.name: oricorio-pom-pom
pokemon.flavorText: This Oricorio has drunk red nectar. If its Trainer gives the wrong order, this passionate Pokémon becomes fiercely angry.

pokemon.name: oricorio-pau
pokemon.flavorText: This Oricorio has drunk red nectar. If its Trainer gives the wrong order, this passionate Pokémon becomes fiercely angry.

pokemon.name: oricorio-sensu
pokemon.flavorText: This Oricorio has drunk red nectar. If its Trainer gives the wrong order, this passionate Pokémon becomes fiercely angry.

pokemon.name: lycanroc-midnight
pokemon.flavorText: With swift movements, this Pokémon gradually backs its prey into a corner. Lycanroc’s fangs are always aimed toward opponents’ weak spots.

pokemon.name: wishiwashi-school
pokemon.flavorText: When it senses danger, its eyes tear up. The sparkle of its tears signals other Wishiwashi to gather.

pokemon.name: lurantis-totem
pokemon.flavorText: The petals on this Pokémon’s arms are thin and super sharp, and they can fire laser beams if Lurantis gathers light first.

pokemon.name: salazzle-totem
pokemon.flavorText: The winner of competitions between Salazzle is decided by which one has the most male Salandit with it.

pokemon.name: minior-orange-meteor
pokemon.flavorText: Although its outer shell is uncommonly durable, the shock of falling to the ground smashes the shell to smithereens.

pokemon.name: minior-yellow-meteor
pokemon.flavorText: Although its outer shell is uncommonly durable, the shock of falling to the ground smashes the shell to smithereens.

pokemon.name: mimikyu-busted
pokemon.flavorText: There was a scientist who peeked under Mimikyu’s old rag in the name of research. The scientist died of a mysterious disease.

pokemon.name: mimikyu-totem-disguised
pokemon.flavorText: There was a scientist who peeked under Mimikyu’s old rag in the name of research. The scientist died of a mysterious disease.

pokemon.name: mimikyu-totem-busted
pokemon.flavorText: There was a scientist who peeked under Mimikyu’s old rag in the name of research. The scientist died of a mysterious disease.

pokemon.name: kommo-o-totem
pokemon.flavorText: Certain ruins have paintings of ancient warriors wearing armor made of Kommo-o scales.

pokemon.name: magearna-original
pokemon.flavorText: Built roughly 500 years ago by a scientist, the part called the Soul-Heart is the actual life-form.

pokemon.name: pikachu-partner-cap
pokemon.flavorText: Possesses cheek sacs in which it stores electricity. This clever forest-dweller roasts tough berries with an electric shock before consuming them.

pokemon.name: marowak-totem
pokemon.flavorText: When this Pokémon evolved, the skull of its mother fused to it. Marowak’s temperament also turned vicious at the same time.

pokemon.name: ribombee-totem
pokemon.flavorText: Ribombee absolutely hate getting wet or rained on. In the cloudy Galar region, they are very seldom seen.

pokemon.name: rockruff-own-tempo
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon intimidates opponents by striking the ground with the rocks on its neck. The moment an opponent flinches, Rockruff attacks.

pokemon.name: lycanroc-dusk
pokemon.flavorText: With swift movements, this Pokémon gradually backs its prey into a corner. Lycanroc’s fangs are always aimed toward opponents’ weak spots.

pokemon.name: araquanid-totem
pokemon.flavorText: It acts as a caretaker for Dewpider, putting them inside its bubble and letting them eat any leftover food.

pokemon.name: togedemaru-totem
pokemon.flavorText: When it’s in trouble, it curls up into a ball, makes its fur spikes stand on end, and then discharges electricity indiscriminately.

pokemon.name: necrozma-dusk
pokemon.flavorText: It needs light to survive, and it goes on a rampage seeking it out. Its laser beams will cut anything to pieces.

pokemon.name: necrozma-dawn
pokemon.flavorText: It needs light to survive, and it goes on a rampage seeking it out. Its laser beams will cut anything to pieces.

pokemon.name: necrozma-ultra
pokemon.flavorText: It needs light to survive, and it goes on a rampage seeking it out. Its laser beams will cut anything to pieces.

pokemon.name: pikachu-starter
pokemon.flavorText: Possesses cheek sacs in which it stores electricity. This clever forest-dweller roasts tough berries with an electric shock before consuming them.

pokemon.name: eevee-starter
pokemon.flavorText: Harbors the potential to evolve into manifold forms. Within Eevee lies the key to the mysteries of Pokémon evolution—I'm certain of it.

pokemon.name: pikachu-world-cap
pokemon.flavorText: Possesses cheek sacs in which it stores electricity. This clever forest-dweller roasts tough berries with an electric shock before consuming them.

pokemon.name: meowth-galar
pokemon.flavorText: It loves to collect shiny things. If it’s in a good mood, it might even let its Trainer have a look at its hoard of treasures.

pokemon.name: ponyta-galar
pokemon.flavorText: These Pokémon live in herds out in the grassland. Newborn foals lack their fiery manes, which will develop about an hour after birth.

pokemon.name: rapidash-galar
pokemon.flavorText: Fiery mane aglow, Rapidash darts like an arrow across the land. This prodigiously swift creature can traverse the vast region of Hisui in a day and a half.

pokemon.name: slowpoke-galar
pokemon.flavorText: When this Pokémon’s tail is soaked in water, sweetness seeps from it. Slowpoke uses this trait to lure in and fish up other Pokémon.

pokemon.name: slowbro-galar
pokemon.flavorText: Being bitten by a Shellder shocked this Pokémon into standing on two legs. If the Shellder lets go, it seems Slowbro will turn back into a Slowpoke.

pokemon.name: farfetchd-galar
pokemon.flavorText: They use a plant stalk as a weapon, but not all of them use it in the same way. Several distinct styles of stalk fighting have been observed.

pokemon.name: weezing-galar
pokemon.flavorText: It can’t suck in air quite as well as a Galarian Weezing, but the toxins it creates are more potent than those of its counterpart.

pokemon.name: mr-mime-galar
pokemon.flavorText: The behavior of this clown-like Pokémon reminds one of pantomime. It creates invisible walls using a force emitted from its fingertips.

pokemon.name: articuno-galar
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon can control ice at will. Articuno is said to live in snowy mountains riddled with permafrost.

pokemon.name: zapdos-galar
pokemon.flavorText: Zapdos is a legendary bird Pokémon. It’s said that when Zapdos rubs its feathers together, lightning will fall immediately after.

pokemon.name: moltres-galar
pokemon.flavorText: There are stories of this Pokémon using its radiant, flame-cloaked wings to light up paths for those lost in the mountains.

pokemon.name: slowking-galar
pokemon.flavorText: Slowking can solve any problem presented to it, but no one can understand a thing Slowking says.

pokemon.name: corsola-galar
pokemon.flavorText: These Pokémon live in warm seas. In prehistoric times, many lived in the oceans around the Galar region as well.

pokemon.name: zigzagoon-galar
pokemon.flavorText: Zigzagoon that adapted to regions outside Galar acquired this appearance. If you’ve lost something, this Pokémon can likely find it.

pokemon.name: linoone-galar
pokemon.flavorText: It uses its explosive speed and razor-sharp claws to bring down prey. Running along winding paths is not its strong suit.

pokemon.name: darumaka-galar
pokemon.flavorText: This popular symbol of good fortune will never fall over in its sleep, no matter how it’s pushed or pulled.

pokemon.name: darmanitan-galar-standard
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon’s power level rises along with the temperature of its fire, which can reach 2,500 degrees Fahrenheit.

pokemon.name: darmanitan-galar-zen
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon’s power level rises along with the temperature of its fire, which can reach 2,500 degrees Fahrenheit.

pokemon.name: yamask-galar
pokemon.flavorText: The spirit of a person from a bygone age became this Pokémon. It rambles through ruins, searching for someone who knows its face.

pokemon.name: stunfisk-galar
pokemon.flavorText: For some reason, this Pokémon smiles slightly when it emits a strong electric current from the yellow markings on its body.

pokemon.name: zygarde-10
pokemon.flavorText: Some say it can change to an even more powerful form when battling those who threaten the ecosystem.

pokemon.name: cramorant-gulping
pokemon.flavorText: This hungry Pokémon swallows Arrokuda whole. Occasionally, it makes a mistake and tries to swallow a Pokémon other than its preferred prey.

pokemon.name: cramorant-gorging
pokemon.flavorText: This hungry Pokémon swallows Arrokuda whole. Occasionally, it makes a mistake and tries to swallow a Pokémon other than its preferred prey.

pokemon.name: toxtricity-low-key
pokemon.flavorText: This short-tempered and aggressive Pokémon chugs stagnant water to absorb any toxins it might contain.

pokemon.name: eiscue-noice
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon keeps its heat-sensitive head cool with ice. It fishes for its food, dangling its single hair into the sea to lure in prey.

pokemon.name: indeedee-female
pokemon.flavorText: Through its horns, it can pick up on the emotions of creatures around it. Positive emotions are the source of its strength.

pokemon.name: morpeko-hangry
pokemon.flavorText: It carries electrically roasted seeds with it as if they’re precious treasures. No matter how much it eats, it always gets hungry again in short order.

pokemon.name: zacian-crowned
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon has slumbered for many years. Some say it’s Zamazenta’s elder sister—others say the two Pokémon are rivals.

pokemon.name: zamazenta-crowned
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon slept for aeons while in the form of a statue. It was asleep for so long, people forgot that it ever existed.

pokemon.name: eternatus-eternamax
pokemon.flavorText: It was inside a meteorite that fell 20,000 years ago. There seems to be a connection between this Pokémon and the Dynamax phenomenon.

pokemon.name: urshifu-rapid-strike
pokemon.flavorText: Inhabiting the mountains of a distant region, this Pokémon races across sheer cliffs, training its legs and refining its moves.

pokemon.name: zarude-dada
pokemon.flavorText: Once the vines on Zarude’s body tear off, they become nutrients in the soil. This helps the plants of the forest grow.

pokemon.name: calyrex-ice
pokemon.flavorText: Calyrex is known in legend as a king that ruled over Galar in ancient times. It has the power to cause hearts to mend and plants to spring forth.

pokemon.name: calyrex-shadow
pokemon.flavorText: Calyrex is known in legend as a king that ruled over Galar in ancient times. It has the power to cause hearts to mend and plants to spring forth.

pokemon.name: venusaur-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: A bewitching aroma wafts from its flower. The fragrance becalms those engaged in a battle.

pokemon.name: charizard-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: Its wings can carry this Pokémon close to an altitude of 4,600 feet. It blows out fire at very high temperatures.

pokemon.name: blastoise-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: The rocket cannons on its shell fire jets of water capable of punching holes through thick steel.

pokemon.name: butterfree-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: It collects honey every day. It rubs honey onto the hairs on its legs to carry it back to its nest.

pokemon.name: pikachu-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: Possesses cheek sacs in which it stores electricity. This clever forest-dweller roasts tough berries with an electric shock before consuming them.

pokemon.name: meowth-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: It loves to collect shiny things. If it’s in a good mood, it might even let its Trainer have a look at its hoard of treasures.

pokemon.name: machamp-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: In close combat, its four arms afford it offensive and defensive supremacy. In but a blink, this valiant Pokémon can overwhelm its foes with more than 1,000 blows from its fists.

pokemon.name: gengar-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: Possesses potential victims' shadows in an effort to steal away the victims' lives. If your shadow begins to laugh, you must take hold of a protective charm posthaste!

pokemon.name: kingler-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: Its oversized claw is very powerful, but when it’s not in battle, the claw just gets in the way.

pokemon.name: lapras-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: Crossing icy seas is no issue for this cold-resistant Pokémon. Its smooth skin is a little cool to the touch.

pokemon.name: eevee-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: Harbors the potential to evolve into manifold forms. Within Eevee lies the key to the mysteries of Pokémon evolution—I'm certain of it.

pokemon.name: snorlax-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: This glutton appears in villages without warning and devours the entirety of their rice granaries—such occurrences have long been counted among the gravest of disasters.

pokemon.name: garbodor-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: The toxic liquid it launches from its right arm is so virulent that it can kill a weakened creature instantly.

pokemon.name: melmetal-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: Centrifugal force is behind the punches of Melmetal’s heavy hex-nut arms. Melmetal is said to deliver the strongest punches of all Pokémon.

pokemon.name: rillaboom-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: The one with the best drumming techniques becomes the boss of the troop. It has a gentle disposition and values harmony among its group.

pokemon.name: cinderace-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: It’s skilled at both offense and defense, and it gets pumped up when cheered on. But if it starts showboating, it could put itself in a tough spot.

pokemon.name: inteleon-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: Its nictitating membranes let it pick out foes’ weak points so it can precisely blast them with water that shoots from its fingertips at Mach 3.

pokemon.name: corviknight-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: With their great intellect and flying skills, these Pokémon very successfully act as the Galar region’s airborne taxi service.

pokemon.name: orbeetle-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: It emits psychic energy to observe and study what’s around it—and what’s around it can include things over six miles away.

pokemon.name: drednaw-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon rapidly extends its retractable neck to sink its sharp fangs into distant enemies and take them down.

pokemon.name: coalossal-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: While it’s engaged in battle, its mountain of coal will burn bright red, sending off sparks that scorch the surrounding area.

pokemon.name: flapple-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: It flies on wings of apple skin and spits a powerful acid. It can also change its shape into that of an apple.

pokemon.name: appletun-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: Its body is covered in sweet nectar, and the skin on its back is especially yummy. Children used to have it as a snack.

pokemon.name: sandaconda-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: Its unique style of coiling allows it to blast sand out of its sand sac more efficiently.

pokemon.name: toxtricity-amped-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: This short-tempered and aggressive Pokémon chugs stagnant water to absorb any toxins it might contain.

pokemon.name: centiskorch-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: While its burning body is already dangerous on its own, this excessively hostile Pokémon also has large and very sharp fangs.

pokemon.name: hatterene-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: If you’re too loud around it, you risk being torn apart by the claws on its tentacle. This Pokémon is also known as the Forest Witch.

pokemon.name: grimmsnarl-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: Its hairs work like muscle fibers. When its hairs unfurl, they latch on to opponents, ensnaring them as tentacles would.

pokemon.name: alcremie-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: When Alcremie is content, the cream it secretes from its hands becomes sweeter and richer.

pokemon.name: copperajah-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: These Pokémon live in herds. Their trunks have incredible grip strength, strong enough to crush giant rocks into powder.

pokemon.name: duraludon-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: The special metal that composes its body is very light, so this Pokémon has considerable agility. It lives in caves because it dislikes the rain.

pokemon.name: urshifu-single-strike-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: Inhabiting the mountains of a distant region, this Pokémon races across sheer cliffs, training its legs and refining its moves.

pokemon.name: urshifu-rapid-strike-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: Inhabiting the mountains of a distant region, this Pokémon races across sheer cliffs, training its legs and refining its moves.

pokemon.name: toxtricity-low-key-gmax
pokemon.flavorText: This short-tempered and aggressive Pokémon chugs stagnant water to absorb any toxins it might contain.

pokemon.name: growlithe-hisui
pokemon.flavorText: They patrol their territory in pairs. I believe the igneous rock components in the fur of this species are the result of volcanic activity in its habitat.

pokemon.name: arcanine-hisui
pokemon.flavorText: Snaps at its foes with fangs cloaked in blazing flame. Despite its bulk, it deftly feints every which way, leading opponents on a deceptively merry chase as it all but dances around them.

pokemon.name: voltorb-hisui
pokemon.flavorText: An enigmatic Pokémon that happens to bear a resemblance to a Poké Ball. When excited, it discharges the electric current it has stored in its belly, then lets out a great, uproarious laugh.

pokemon.name: electrode-hisui
pokemon.flavorText: The tissue on the surface of its body is curiously similar in composition to an Apricorn. When irritated, this Pokémon lets loose an electric current equal to 20 lightning bolts.

pokemon.name: typhlosion-hisui
pokemon.flavorText: Said to purify lost, forsaken souls with its flames and guide them to the afterlife. I believe its form has been influenced by the energy of the sacred mountain towering at Hisui's center.

pokemon.name: qwilfish-hisui
pokemon.flavorText: Fishers detest this troublesome Pokémon because it sprays poison from its spines, getting it everywhere. A different form of Qwilfish lives in other regions.

pokemon.name: sneasel-hisui
pokemon.flavorText: Its sturdy, curved claws are ideal for traversing precipitous cliffs. From the tips of these claws drips a venom that infiltrates the nerves of any prey caught in Sneasel's grasp.

pokemon.name: samurott-hisui
pokemon.flavorText: Hard of heart and deft of blade, this rare form of Samurott is a product of the Pokémon's evolution in the region of Hisui. Its turbulent blows crash into foes like ceaseless pounding waves.

pokemon.name: lilligant-hisui
pokemon.flavorText: I suspect that its well-developed legs are the result of a life spent on mountains covered in deep snow. The scent it exudes from its flower crown heartens those in proximity.

pokemon.name: zorua-hisui
pokemon.flavorText: A once-departed soul, returned to life in Hisui. Derives power from resentment, which rises as energy atop its head and takes on the forms of foes. In this way, Zorua vents lingering malice.

pokemon.name: zoroark-hisui
pokemon.flavorText: With its disheveled white fur, it looks like an embodiment of death. Heedless of its own safety, Zoroark attacks its nemeses with a bitter energy so intense, it lacerates Zoroark's own body.

pokemon.name: braviary-hisui
pokemon.flavorText: Screaming a bloodcurdling battle cry, this huge and ferocious bird Pokémon goes out on the hunt. It blasts lakes with shock waves, then scoops up any prey that float to the water's surface.

pokemon.name: sliggoo-hisui
pokemon.flavorText: A creature given to melancholy. I suspect its metallic shell developed as a result of the mucus on its skin reacting with the iron in Hisui's water.

pokemon.name: goodra-hisui
pokemon.flavorText: Able to freely control the hardness of its metallic shell. It loathes solitude and is extremely clingy—it will fume and run riot if those dearest to it ever leave its side.

pokemon.name: avalugg-hisui
pokemon.flavorText: The armor of ice covering its lower jaw puts steel to shame and can shatter rocks with ease. This Pokémon barrels along steep mountain paths, cleaving through the deep snow.

pokemon.name: decidueye-hisui
pokemon.flavorText: The air stored inside the rachises of Decidueye's feathers insulates the Pokémon against Hisui's extreme cold. This is firm proof that evolution can be influenced by environment.

pokemon.name: dialga-origin
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon is revered as a deity in Hisuian legend. The birth of Dialga was what caused the vast river of time to begin flowing in our world.

pokemon.name: palkia-origin
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon is feared as a deity in Hisuian legend. The birth of Palkia was what caused the walls of our world to disappear, creating a sky that spans for infinity.

pokemon.name: basculin-white-striped
pokemon.flavorText: Though it differs from other Basculin in several respects, including demeanor—this one is gentle—I have categorized it as a regional form given the vast array of shared qualities.

pokemon.name: basculegion-female
pokemon.flavorText: Clads itself in the souls of comrades that perished before fulfilling their goals of journeying upstream. No other species throughout all Hisui's rivers is Basculegion's equal.

pokemon.name: enamorus-therian
pokemon.flavorText: When it flies to this land from across the sea, the bitter winter comes to an end. According to legend, this Pokémon's love gives rise to the budding of fresh life across Hisui.

pokemon.name: tauros-paldea-combat-breed
pokemon.flavorText: The Tauros of the Galar region are volatile in nature, and they won’t allow people to ride on their backs.

pokemon.name: tauros-paldea-blaze-breed
pokemon.flavorText: The Tauros of the Galar region are volatile in nature, and they won’t allow people to ride on their backs.

pokemon.name: tauros-paldea-aqua-breed
pokemon.flavorText: The Tauros of the Galar region are volatile in nature, and they won’t allow people to ride on their backs.

pokemon.name: wooper-paldea
pokemon.flavorText: When walking on land, it covers its body with a poisonous film that keeps its skin from dehydrating.

pokemon.name: oinkologne-female
pokemon.flavorText: It entrances female Pokémon with the sweet, alluring scent that wafts from all over its body.

pokemon.name: dudunsparce-three-segment
pokemon.flavorText: It drives enemies out of its nest by sucking in enough air to fill its long, narrow lungs, then releasing the air in an intense blast.

pokemon.name: palafin-hero
pokemon.flavorText: Its physical capabilities are no different than a Finizen’s, but when its allies are in danger, it transforms and powers itself up.

pokemon.name: maushold-family-of-three
pokemon.flavorText: The larger pair protects the little ones during battles. When facing strong opponents, the whole group will join the fight.

pokemon.name: tatsugiri-droopy
pokemon.flavorText: Tatsugiri is an extremely cunning Pokémon. It feigns weakness to lure in prey, then orders its partner to attack.

pokemon.name: tatsugiri-stretchy
pokemon.flavorText: Tatsugiri is an extremely cunning Pokémon. It feigns weakness to lure in prey, then orders its partner to attack.

pokemon.name: squawkabilly-blue-plumage
pokemon.flavorText: Green-feathered flocks hold the most sway. When they’re out searching for food in the mornings and evenings, it gets very noisy.

pokemon.name: squawkabilly-yellow-plumage
pokemon.flavorText: Green-feathered flocks hold the most sway. When they’re out searching for food in the mornings and evenings, it gets very noisy.

pokemon.name: squawkabilly-white-plumage
pokemon.flavorText: Green-feathered flocks hold the most sway. When they’re out searching for food in the mornings and evenings, it gets very noisy.

pokemon.name: gimmighoul-roaming
pokemon.flavorText: It lives inside an old treasure chest. Sometimes it gets left in shop corners since no one realizes it’s actually a Pokémon.

pokemon.name: koraidon-limited-build
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon resembles Cyclizar, but it is far burlier and more ferocious. Nothing is known about its ecology or other features.

pokemon.name: koraidon-sprinting-build
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon resembles Cyclizar, but it is far burlier and more ferocious. Nothing is known about its ecology or other features.

pokemon.name: koraidon-swimming-build
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon resembles Cyclizar, but it is far burlier and more ferocious. Nothing is known about its ecology or other features.

pokemon.name: koraidon-gliding-build
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon resembles Cyclizar, but it is far burlier and more ferocious. Nothing is known about its ecology or other features.

pokemon.name: miraidon-low-power-mode
pokemon.flavorText: This seems to be the Iron Serpent mentioned in an old book. The Iron Serpent is said to have turned the land to ash with its lightning.

pokemon.name: miraidon-drive-mode
pokemon.flavorText: This seems to be the Iron Serpent mentioned in an old book. The Iron Serpent is said to have turned the land to ash with its lightning.

pokemon.name: miraidon-aquatic-mode
pokemon.flavorText: This seems to be the Iron Serpent mentioned in an old book. The Iron Serpent is said to have turned the land to ash with its lightning.

pokemon.name: miraidon-glide-mode
pokemon.flavorText: This seems to be the Iron Serpent mentioned in an old book. The Iron Serpent is said to have turned the land to ash with its lightning.

pokemon.name: ursaluna-bloodmoon
pokemon.flavorText: I believe it was Hisui's swampy terrain that gave Ursaluna its burly physique and newfound capacity to manipulate peat at will.

pokemon.name: ogerpon-wellspring-mask
pokemon.flavorText: This mischief-loving Pokémon is full of curiosity. It battles by drawing out the type-based energy contained within its masks.

pokemon.name: ogerpon-hearthflame-mask
pokemon.flavorText: This mischief-loving Pokémon is full of curiosity. It battles by drawing out the type-based energy contained within its masks.

pokemon.name: ogerpon-cornerstone-mask
pokemon.flavorText: This mischief-loving Pokémon is full of curiosity. It battles by drawing out the type-based energy contained within its masks.

pokemon.name: terapagos-terastal
pokemon.flavorText: It’s thought that this Pokémon lived in ancient Paldea until it got caught in seismic shifts and went extinct.

pokemon.name: terapagos-stellar
pokemon.flavorText: It’s thought that this Pokémon lived in ancient Paldea until it got caught in seismic shifts and went extinct.

pokemon.name: clefable-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Legend says that on clear, quiet nights, it listens for the voices of its kin living on the moon. I, too, often think of my homeland, so far away.

pokemon.name: victreebel-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Lures prey with the sweet aroma of honey. Swallowed whole, the prey is dissolved in a day, bones and all.

pokemon.name: starmie-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Starmie swims by spinning its body at high speed. As this Pokémon cruises through the ocean, it absorbs tiny plankton.

pokemon.name: dragonite-mega
pokemon.flavorText: This Pokémon is known as the Sea Incarnate. Figureheads that resemble Dragonite decorate the bows of many ships.

pokemon.name: meganium-mega
pokemon.flavorText: The fragrance of Meganium’s flower soothes and calms emotions. In battle, this Pokémon gives off more of its becalming scent to blunt the foe’s fighting spirit.

pokemon.name: feraligatr-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Feraligatr intimidates its foes by opening its huge mouth. In battle, it will kick the ground hard with its thick and powerful hind legs to charge at the foe at an incredible speed.

pokemon.name: skarmory-mega
pokemon.flavorText: People fashion swords from Skarmory’s shed feathers, so this Pokémon is a popular element in heraldic designs.

pokemon.name: froslass-mega
pokemon.flavorText: A Pokémon inhabited by the soul of a woman who died bearing a grudge in the snowy mountains. Legends of Froslass placing deathly curses on misbehaving men send shivers down my spine.

pokemon.name: emboar-mega
pokemon.flavorText: It has mastered fast and powerful fighting moves. It grows a beard of fire.

pokemon.name: excadrill-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Known as the Drill King, this Pokémon can tunnel through the terrain at speeds of over 90 mph.

pokemon.name: scolipede-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Scolipede engage in fierce territorial battles with Centiskorch. At the end of one of these battles, the victor makes a meal of the loser.

pokemon.name: scrafty-mega
pokemon.flavorText: While mostly known for having the temperament of an aggressive ruffian, this Pokémon takes very good care of its family, friends, and territory.

pokemon.name: eelektross-mega
pokemon.flavorText: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.

pokemon.name: chandelure-mega
pokemon.flavorText: In homes illuminated by Chandelure instead of lights, funerals were a constant occurrence— or so it’s said.

pokemon.name: chesnaught-mega
pokemon.flavorText: When it takes a defensive posture with its fists guarding its face, it could withstand a bomb blast.

pokemon.name: delphox-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Using psychic power, it generates a fiery vortex of 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit, incinerating foes swept into this whirl of flame.

pokemon.name: greninja-mega
pokemon.flavorText: It appears and vanishes with a ninja’s grace. It toys with its enemies using swift movements, while slicing them with throwing stars of sharpest water.

pokemon.name: pyroar-mega
pokemon.flavorText: The temperature of its breath is over 10,000 degrees Fahrenheit, but Pyroar doesn’t use it on its prey. This Pokémon prefers to eat raw meat.

pokemon.name: floette-mega
pokemon.flavorText: It gives its own power to flowers, pouring its heart into caring for them. Floette never forgives anyone who messes up a flower bed.

pokemon.name: malamar-mega
pokemon.flavorText: It’s said that Malamar’s hypnotic powers played a role in certain history-changing events.

pokemon.name: barbaracle-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Having an eye on each palm allows it to keep watch in all directions. In a pinch, its limbs start to act on their own to ensure the enemy’s defeat.

pokemon.name: dragalge-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Dragalge generates dragon energy by sticking the plume on its head out above the ocean’s surface and bathing it in sunlight.

pokemon.name: hawlucha-mega
pokemon.flavorText: It always strikes a pose before going for its finishing move. Sometimes opponents take advantage of that time to counterattack.

pokemon.name: zygarde-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Some say it can change to an even more powerful form when battling those who threaten the ecosystem.

pokemon.name: drampa-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Drampa is a kind and friendly Pokémon—up until it’s angered. When that happens, it stirs up a gale and flattens everything around.

pokemon.name: falinks-mega
pokemon.flavorText: The six of them work together as one Pokémon. Teamwork is also their battle strategy, and they constantly change their formation as they fight.

pokemon.name: raichu-mega-x
pokemon.flavorText: It can discharge bursts of electricity exceeding 100,000 volts— a single strike with that amount of power would incapacitate one of the Copperajah of my homeland.

pokemon.name: raichu-mega-y
pokemon.flavorText: It can discharge bursts of electricity exceeding 100,000 volts— a single strike with that amount of power would incapacitate one of the Copperajah of my homeland.

pokemon.name: chimecho-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Can emit waves of air powerful enough to knock out prey taller than itself. I hypothesize that it amplifies the faint sound of wind within its body.

pokemon.name: absol-mega-z
pokemon.flavorText: Because of this Pokémon’s ability to detect danger, people mistook Absol as a bringer of doom.

pokemon.name: staraptor-mega
pokemon.flavorText: It has left the flock, having gained strength enough to survive on its own. The astounding force with which Staraptor flies through the air allows it to carry away large, burly targets.

pokemon.name: garchomp-mega-z
pokemon.flavorText: Soars across the heavens at blinding speed—a magnificent sight! It has a feral disposition. Utmost caution is required if one meets a Garchomp out in the wilds.

pokemon.name: lucario-mega-z
pokemon.flavorText: A most gallant-looking creature. It emits energy waves and controls them with precision, using them to sense even faraway beings. I have given the name ”aura” to this power.

pokemon.name: heatran-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Stories tell of this Pokémon being birthed from the boiling magma within Mount Coronet. Its molten-steel body holds many mysteries.

pokemon.name: darkrai-mega
pokemon.flavorText: On a moonless night, a strange incident occurred in which every one of a village's inhabitants suffered nightmares. The villagers attested that Darkrai appeared before them in these nightmares.

pokemon.name: golurk-mega
pokemon.flavorText: There’s a theory that inside Golurk is a perpetual motion machine that produces limitless energy, but this belief hasn’t been proven.

pokemon.name: meowstic-mega
pokemon.flavorText: The defensive instinct of the males is strong. It’s when they’re protecting themselves or their partners that they unleash their full power.

pokemon.name: crabominable-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Before it stops to think, it just starts pummeling. There are records of its turning back avalanches with a flurry of punches.

pokemon.name: golisopod-mega
pokemon.flavorText: They live in sunken ships or in holes in the seabed. When Golisopod and Grapploct battle, the loser becomes the winner’s meal.

pokemon.name: magearna-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Built roughly 500 years ago by a scientist, the part called the Soul-Heart is the actual life-form.

pokemon.name: magearna-original-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Built roughly 500 years ago by a scientist, the part called the Soul-Heart is the actual life-form.

pokemon.name: zeraora-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Electricity sparks from the pads on its limbs. Wherever Zeraora runs, lightning flashes and thunder echoes.

pokemon.name: scovillain-mega
pokemon.flavorText: The green head has turned vicious due to the spicy chemicals stimulating its brain. Once it goes on a rampage, there is no stopping it.

pokemon.name: glimmora-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Glimmora’s petals are made of crystallized poison energy. It has recently become evident that these petals resemble Tera Jewels.

pokemon.name: tatsugiri-curly-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Tatsugiri is an extremely cunning Pokémon. It feigns weakness to lure in prey, then orders its partner to attack.

pokemon.name: tatsugiri-droopy-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Tatsugiri is an extremely cunning Pokémon. It feigns weakness to lure in prey, then orders its partner to attack.

pokemon.name: tatsugiri-stretchy-mega
pokemon.flavorText: Tatsugiri is an extremely cunning Pokémon. It feigns weakness to lure in prey, then orders its partner to attack.

pokemon.name: baxcalibur-mega
pokemon.flavorText: It launches itself into battle by flipping upside down and spewing frigid air from its mouth. It finishes opponents off with its dorsal blade.
